race.comment: Open race. HUSTLE IN HEELS (5) is a lightly raced mare who resumed for her second campaign, winning over the 955m at Cranbourne in good time. She did win her only start around here on debut and with the added fitness and natural improvement she should take plenty of beating again. SKIPJACK (2) resumes. He took on some handy races at the back end of last campaign and ran well. His 1000m record reads very well for this and he can have last crack. MISTY LEGEND (4) resumes for the new yard, formerly with the Hawkes in Sydney. He did win first up at Warwick Farm over this trip in a BM72. He's absolutely good enough to win this, watch the late betting. YOU'RE TWO VAIN (3) is an unbeaten gelding who resumed with a comfortable win in a Class 3 at Corowa. This is harder but his two wins last time in suggested he'd be measuring up to city grade. FULLY CALCULATED (7) can sneak into the minors.
